Subject: Re: [T2] torque values for the sump plate, oil temp sender?

On 3/30/05 7:43 PM, "Jack Hattaway" <jack(-at-)law.utah.edu> wrote:

> Is 9ft pounds the correct torque for the oil sump plate? I've come into
> possession of a 914 "taco" plate, and, as best I can tell from the
> Bentley manual, the VW version of the plate is called an oil cover plate.

9 ft. lbs for the single bolt on the strainer plate, 5 ft. lbs. on the two
bolts for the taco plate.

> I have a new O-ring for the plate. Will it be sufficient, or am I better
> served to use some flavor of gasket adhesive as well?

O-ring is sufficient.
 
> Is there a range to which the sender unit should be torqued?

Torque it to the plate in a vise before mounting and with a crush washer
apply 22 ft. lbs.

